Вакансія від 20 березня 2020
Advertising Manager, менеджер по интернет-рекламе
20 000 – 26 000 грн · Negotiable, based on skills
Alirm LLC
Роздрібна торгівля;
10–50 співробітників
Київ, Кловський узвіз, 7.
1,7 км від центру ·
На мапі
Повна зайнятість.
Досвід роботи від 2 років.
Вища освіта.
Опис вакансії
We are looking for the highly professional and pro-active Advertizing Manager to join our Kyiv based team. This is a great chance to be involved in a fast-growing company and become a valuable part of the international team.Responsibilities:
Campaigns creating, managing & developing: search, display, re-marketing, optimization;
Maintaining and monitoring keyword bids, account daily and monthly budget caps, impression share, quality score, conversion rates, seasonal/geographical trends, search queries, product pages/landing pages, conversion funnel, etc.;
Reporting (daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly) and analyzing with conclusions and suggestions for improvement major metrics, goals tracking, revenue tracking, etc.;
Keeping pace with search engine and Advertising industry trends and developments;
Manage and monitor Ad-spend: Identify opportunities to increase ROI on spend and consistently test and learn to maximize results;
Conduct research and trend analysis to create effective Ads campaigns;
Direct and handle new paid search campaigns, ad groups, and accounts and aid in the creation of paid search marketing initiatives;
Deep dive into analytics data to form the basis of campaign strategies and optimization;
New product launch support — auto campaigns run and testing, analysis, keyword research;
Suggest and develop new campaigns.
Requirements:
Excellent command of English and extraordinary communication skills;
Motivation, pro-activity, and enthusiasm are a must;
Proven experience with Google Ads, Bing, Yahoo AdCenter, AdWords, Facebook;
Strong quantitative and qualitative analytical skills and open technical mind;
Project management skills — ability to detail out a plan and execute on a deadline;
Ability to handle multiple tasks in a fast-paced environment, under tight deadlines;
Proficient in MS Office (particularly Excel).
Work Conditions:
Full-time office job 5 days, 40 hours week;
Competitive stable compensation;
Career advancement opportunities within the company and personal development;
Work schedule: 12 pm — 9 pm (UTC+3);
Official contract.
